      "AdditionalInfo": {
        "type": "text",
        "dtype": "String",
        "label": "Effect Additional Information",
        "value": "<p align=\"center\"><em><span lang=\"en-us\" xml:lang=\"en-us\">Example</span></em></p>\n<p align=\"center\"><em><span lang=\"en-us\" xml:lang=\"en-us\">I am attempting to use a&nbsp;<abbr title=\"Item, Vehicle, or Weapon\"><abbr title=\"Item, Vehicle, or Weapon\">Possession</abbr></abbr>&nbsp;which requires two&nbsp;<abbr title=\"Artistry, Expertise, Gymnastics, Operation and Weapons\"><abbr title=\"Artistry, Expertise, Gymnastics, Operation and Weapons\">Skills</abbr></abbr>&nbsp;I do not possess at level 2. The total reduction to the roll would be &ndash; 40%. My&nbsp;<abbr title=\"A Player's Character\"><abbr title=\"A Player's Character\">Protagonist</abbr></abbr>&nbsp;has already successfully activated Beginner&rsquo;s Luck and accumulated&nbsp;</span></em><em><span lang=\"en-us\" xml:lang=\"en-us\"><abbr title=\"Level of Success\"><span class=\"ipsEmoji\"><abbr title=\"Level of Success\">‚úîÔ∏è</abbr></span></abbr><abbr title=\"Level of Success\"><span class=\"ipsEmoji\"><abbr title=\"Level of Success\">‚úîÔ∏è</abbr></span></abbr></span></em><em><span lang=\"en-us\" xml:lang=\"en-us\">. As I result I ignore the first &ndash; 10% reduction from my initial roll. I can spend&nbsp;</span></em><strong><em><span lang=\"en-us\" xml:lang=\"en-us\"><abbr title=\"Spent Level of Success\"><span class=\"ipsEmoji\"><abbr title=\"Spent Level of Success\">‚úÖ</abbr></span></abbr></span></em></strong><em><span lang=\"en-us\" xml:lang=\"en-us\">&nbsp;</span></em><strong><em><span lang=\"en-us\" xml:lang=\"en-us\"><abbr title=\"Spent Level of Success\"><span class=\"ipsEmoji\"><abbr title=\"Spent Level of Success\">‚úÖ</abbr></span></abbr></span></em></strong><span lang=\"en-us\" xml:lang=\"en-us\">&nbsp;</span><em><span lang=\"en-us\" xml:lang=\"en-us\">to further reduce the reduction by a total of &ndash; 30%. Therefore I can attempt that action with a total of &ndash; 10% reduction.</span></em></p>"
